MURPHY v. HURLEY et al. (No. 2.) (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, Second Department. February 21, 1913.) Appeal from Special Term, Kings County. Action by John J. Murphy against William S. Hurley and others. Plaintiff appeals from an order. Affirmed.

Argued before JENKS, P. J., and BURR, THOMAS, CARR, and WOODWARD, JJ.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed, with $10 costs and disbursements, on the authority of Murphy v. Hurley (Appeal No. 1) 140 N. Y. Supp. 614, decided herewith.
